Definition: A structured set of questions intended to guide the collection of answers from end-users. Questionnaires provide detailed control over order, presentation, phraseology and grouping to allow coherent, consistent data collection.

Short: Elements that belong to all information items.
Definition: Elements that belong to all information items.

Short: A human language, spoken or written.
Definition: A human language, spoken or written.

Short: A set of rules under which this content was created
Definition: A set of rules under which this content was created

Short: A human-readable narrative, potentially including images, that contains a summary of the resource, and may be used to represent the content of the resource to a human.
Definition: A human-readable narrative, potentially including images, that contains a summary of the resource, and may be used to represent the content of the resource to a human.

Short: A state that relates to the workflow or interpretation of this resource. Certain status values can modify the meaning of the resource, for example, entered-in-error. When a boolean value is used, Status of true indicates the record is active, false means inactive.
Definition: A state that relates to the workflow or interpretation of this resource. Certain status values can modify the meaning of the resource, for example, entered-in-error. When a boolean value is used, Status of true indicates the record is active, false means inactive.

Short: Business identifier or external id for this resource.
Definition: Business identifier or external id for this resource.

Short: A unique URL on which the device may be contacted directly.
Definition: A unique URL on which the device may be contacted directly.

Short: A string associated with the product that identifies a particular release iteration.
Definition: A string associated with the product that identifies a particular release iteration.

Short: The name as plain unstructured or semi-structured text.
Definition: The name as plain unstructured or semi-structured text.

Short: A distinguishing word or group of words naming an item.
Definition: A distinguishing word or group of words naming an item.

Short: Indicates the source of information in the case the Entry has been created by logical extension or modification of one or more source entries.
Definition: Indicates the source of information in the case the Entry has been created by logical extension or modification of one or more source entries.

Short: A Boolean value to indicate that the item is for testing purposes (or education/evaluation/marketing) and is not intended to be used for genuine usage.
Definition: A Boolean value to indicate that the item is for testing purposes (or education/evaluation/marketing) and is not intended to be used for genuine usage.

Short: Resource that can be subject of QuestionnaireResponse
Definition: Resource that can be subject of QuestionnaireResponse

Short: The most recent date the information item was changed.
Definition: The most recent date the information item was changed.

Short: The name of the organization or individual that published this item.
Definition: The name of the organization or individual that published this item.

Short: Describes an individual and how to reach them.
Definition: Describes an individual and how to reach them.

Short: A description of the purpose of the item.
Definition: A description of the purpose of the item.

Short: The content was developed with a focus and intent of supporting the contexts that are listed. These contexts may be general categories (gender, age, ...) or may be references to specific programs (insurance plans, studies, ...) and may be used to assist with indexing and searching for appropriate questionnaire instances.
Definition: The content was developed with a focus and intent of supporting the contexts that are listed. These contexts may be general categories (gender, age, ...) or may be references to specific programs (insurance plans, studies, ...) and may be used to assist with indexing and searching for appropriate questionnaire instances.

Short: The country, state or other region taking legal responsibility.
Definition: The country, state or other region taking legal responsibility.

Short: A description of the purpose of the item.
Definition: A description of the purpose of the item.

Short: A rights statement relating legal restrictions on the use and publishing of the item.
Definition: A rights statement relating legal restrictions on the use and publishing of the item.

Short: The date on which the item was officiallly deemed acceptable by the publisher.
Definition: The date on which the item was officiallly deemed acceptable by the publisher.

Short: The most recent date the item was reviewed.
Definition: The most recent date the item was reviewed.

Short: The date and time span for which something is active, valid, or in force.
Definition: The date and time span for which something is active, valid, or in force.

Short: The main type identifier for a lab, procedure, condition, etc., usually drawn from a controlled vocabulary.
Definition: The main type identifier for a lab, procedure, condition, etc., usually drawn from a controlled vocabulary.

Short: Questions and sections within the Questionnaire.
Definition: Questions and sections within the Questionnaire.
